No fewer than thirteen men who claimed to be from a particular part of the country were yesterday intercepted by men of the Amotekun Corps, Osun command from entering the state. The alleged intruders who were intercepted along Ibadan/Ife expressway were said to have divided themselves into groups armed with various weapons that includes machetes, cutlasses, shovels and assorted charms. According to the director, Amotekun Corps in Osun, Comrade Amitolu Shittu, when interrogated, they claimed they were labourers at mining sites in Osun but could not explain why they came with weapons and assorted charms and tried to enter into the state illegally. It would be recalled that the directive by President Muhammadu Buhari and Governor Adegboyega Oyetola on border closure to forestall the spread of the dreaded COVID-19 is still in force.  